            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>chopped cherry tomatoes</strong>,<strong> sliced onion</strong>,<strong> cucumber</strong>, <strong>parsley</strong> and<strong> mint</strong> to the <strong>cooked bulgur wheat</strong></p><p>Add your<strong> dried oregano</strong>, <strong>juice</strong> of<strong> half</strong> your <strong>lemon[s]</strong>, the <strong>remaining garlic</strong> (don't like raw garlic? Just add a little!), 2 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[3 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[4 tbsp] </span><strong>olive oil</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p><p>Give everything a gentle mix up – this is your<strong> Greek bulgur salad</strong></p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
